    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Mirror records between tools with HubSpot and Notion 24/7\n\n**Pattern:** Two-System Sync · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nMirror records between tools with HubSpot and Notion 24/7. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual two-way sync is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nDaily Schedule → Pull Side A (HubSpot) → Diff the Two Systems → Create Missing in Notion → Gather Sync Results → Stamp Processing Time → Guard Non-Empty sourceId → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to two-system sync without manual effort\n- Anyone automating two-way sync in data\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Scales without extra headcount\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: HubSpot private-app token; Notion integration token; Twilio SID + token.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
